channel.description:
well, This was in one of my Mom's classes, And I saw it, They only used to question what was what in the video with the inner workings of cell biology. [url=http://bioweb.wku.edu/courses/Biol120/Section2/cell.swf]http://bioweb.wku.edu/courses/Biol120/Section2/cell.swf[/url] is the place, You can't find a higher quality version(or so I think) or the same version anywhere else(or so I think..) BTW, Proteins are cool in how they work(look at the thing carrying the Vacuole on the green bridge(forgot the name of that))
Tell me what you think ;D
Edit: They have a lame server, so it may lag due to multiple access

item.dc:creator: @kloplop321 kloplop321
item.description:
@kloplop321 wrote:

It may make you feel weird that you(most likely) have E-Coli(or w/e) already in your bowels, but isn’t active. You also have plenty of bacteria in your system, both good, and bad(or just lazy).

This is just a Short movie showing the inner-workings of your cells, Some of the stuff you see in there doesn’t have to do with the actual working of the cell, but rather something cool to exaggerate. Remember, Proteins are cool!
